name: Fish Hatchery Ultimate
description:
Friendly pickup game, all levels and abilities welcome.

We play from the Tuesday after the start of Daylight Savings Time (March 15th in 2016) until the Tuesday before DST ends (November 3rd 2016.) We also play on Thursdays.

Send Email to bschlieder@gmail.com to confirm sufficient players early and late in season.

The location will be at the fish hatchery.  To get there go south on Cedar Crest Blvd. from route 78, turn left at Fish Hatchery road (third light south of 78.)  Continue on Fish Hatchery road for about 1/4 mile.

On the left side of the road is the fish hatchery.  Turn right at the bottom of the hill, field is on your left.  Just look for people throwing discs.

name: Ambler Ultimate
description:
Ambler Ultimate has the distinction of being the longest running pickup Ultimate game in the world. It was started as a place for beginners to learn the game away from the pressures of the competitive Ultimate league. Although we now have players of all skill levels the game retains that initial flavor. Currently we are playing (Thanks Myers!) at the Temple University Ambler Campus. We play on Wednesday nights Spring through Fall during Daylight Savings Time(March 23 - October 1st). Play usually starts anywhere from 5:45pm to 6pm. Beginners are not only welcomed but are encouraged to come out. We alter the rules to take the pressure off if you are a beginner.
Bring a white shirt, and a dark shirt with you so we can divide the teams evenly and don't forget to bring water to drink!

If the game is listed in the calendar and there aren't any posts below that indicate it's cancelled then the game is on.

Union City Ultimate is a newer group looking to expand and meet new people! We play on a turf soccer field under lights and we play for two hours. Union City Leisure Services runs and manages the games at Shorty Garcia Park at the intersection of 7th street and Decoto Rd. 

Because of the location and reservation of the field, there is a small participation fee. $4/night or $20/season. Seasons are similar to quarters of the year.

name: Ultimate Fridays Midday on the UC Berkeley Campus
description:
Every Friday 12:15-2:00pm (except in rain)

Warmup at 12:15, Game at 12:30. Real Time. Not "Ultimate Time."

You must join our group https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/pickup-ultimate-at-cal to get the weekly field announcement the day before (we have three fields) with a request for RSVP's. The RSVP's will be tallied and you will get notice by 10:00 am each game day. You don't need a google account to be part of the group. Just send us your email address, and we'll add you.

Join in a relaxed pickup ultimate Frisbee game, open to players with all levels of experience. Our emphasis is on fun, and getting a great workout. Cleats are OK, although most of us don't use them. Bring your own water. This pickup game has met weekly since 1993.

More info and contact:  https://sites.google.com/site/calcampusultimate/

Join our Facebook group (and invite others) - that helps us spread the news: https://www.facebook.com/groups/158092704285218/

description:

Our usual field is located directly behind the Edmonton South-East Senior's Association (9350 82 St), though we have no connection to them.

name: Peterson AFB Ultimate
description:
We have a pretty easy going group with a range of ages.  We try to play twice a week. One of the usual coordinators will send an email invitation to play.  We will call GAME On when 8 people commit (teams 4 vs 4).

Important: If you commit, we ask that you please show.  We want to respect everyone's time, especially since some people come from off base.  If you can’t commit but are interested, a “maybe” will also be taken into consideration when deciding GAME ON or OFF.   If you’ve committed and have to back out, please try to let us know prior to 1000 on game day.

name: Ultimate Frisbee Bahrain
description:
Weekly co-ed pick-up game played on Friday on the U.S. Navy Base field.  All genders, talent levels, and nationalities are welcome!

WHEN:  5pm-7pm or 6pm-8pm (times vary by season and the accurate schedule is posted on Facebook).

WHAT TO BRING:  (1) white shirt; (2) dark shirt; (3) water; (4) Bahrain CPR or passport if not in the military; (5) BD3 for BBQ

ACCESS TO BASE:  If not a military person, you will need a military escort to gain entry into the military base.  Arrive at the base's main gate (shown on map) 15 minutes prior to game time with a Bahrain CPR or passport.  A military person will be there to escort you onto base.  If you are late, there may not be anyone there.  So please be punctual.

SOCIALIZING:  BBQ afterward.  Bring BD3 if you wish to join us. 

OTHER DETAILS:  See Facebook for most up-to-date schedule.
html_description:

name: Evanston Ultimate Pickup
sunday_time: 1pm to 4pm (check for polls in winter at website)
description:
Please join https://www.facebook.com/groups/287963344693753/
For up to date information.

We are a group that plays pickup ultimate in Evanston IL.
We are mainly intermediate players with some members that have played competitively, but want to play a more relaxed/friendlier game. 
On Sundays we meet at 1pm.
On Tuesdays and Thursdays we are meeting at 5:30. 
As to WHERE we are playing: 

During the summer months (6/11 to 8/18), we are playing at New Trier East, on the fields just behind the school on the north side.  New Trier East is located a few blocks east of Green Bay and Winnetka in Willmette.

During the fall/spring for weekday games, we are currently meeting at Elks park, which is a few blocks south of the South Boulevard stop along the west side of the el tracks in Evanston.

During the winter months, we meet on Sundays at 1pm at Long Field, which is at the corner of Lincoln and Sheridan in Evanston.

name: Sedgwick County Ultimate
description:
We're a little more casual than some of the other groups you'll find around town. So if you're getting your butt kicked elsewhere by young college guys with 3.8 second 40-yard-dash times and 36-inch verticals or just want to try a slightly more relaxed game, I propose you come hang out and play a game or two with us.

This game has been played at this time and location for over 15 years (or so I hear), even in snow. We play almost every Sunday. Once you get some contact info from other players, you can text or email someone to see who all might or might not be playing that day/week if you just want to be sure we're playing.

description:

We play three or four times a week at times and places which vary with the seasons, including indoors in a dome during the winter.  Those games cost $20 for gainfully employed adults, but the first one is free.   As of June 2016, we play Tuesday and Friday mornings at 6:00 at the New York Athletic Club on Shore Rd.  (see map on website), and Wednesday nights ($10 for lights) and Sunday afternoons at Glover Field (likewise).

name: Milpitas Ultimate
description:
Games are played every first (1st) and third (3rd) Saturday of the month (some exceptions).  For confirmation on event dates please check the Facebook group page.

Friendly game where skill levels range from rookie to intermediate.  Field is smaller than regulation.  Age limit requirement is high school and above; (majority are adults).  First pull is at 1:00 PM so please arrive on time and be ready to start play at 1.  You will need to bring a white and a dark shirt for team coordination and be able to change if needed.  Cleats are recommended but not necessary; no metal spikes.  We play rain or shine... or mud!

If you'd like to see some videos from our previous games, the following link contains a playlist of monthly highlights: http://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLXVS90xLX000HovVXce3bv_QgU1AkI17d

name: Amsterdam casual pickup
description:
During the winter time (From October to April) we meet Sunday afternoons at 2:30pm in Museumplein, in the large grassy area behind the van Gogh Museum.

During daylight savings (from April to October) we meet Thursday at 6pm in Erasmuspark and then BBQ afterwards if the weather is cooperative.

People start throwing around 6 or 6:30 and then we play for a couple hours.

We try to play rain or shine, especially in the summer season. The only thing that normally stops us is extreme high wind. Weather forecasts in the Netherlands are notoriously unreliable, so we won't call the game off until that afternoon. Most years the game is never called off in the summer season. Check the Facebook page at https://www.facebook.com/groups/ultimate.amsterdam/ for confirmation.

We have jerseys so you don't need to worry about shirt colors.

The game is pretty casual, and people of all skill levels are welcome. We have everyone from beginners to veterans. Cleats are a good idea, but not necessary.
html_description:
Amsterdam casual pickup

Website: https://www.facebook.com/groups/ultimate.amsterdam/

Thursdays: 18:00

Fields: Grass, cleats allowed

name: Key Biscayne Ultimate
description:
We've been playing at Key Biscayne and Virginia Key for over 10 years now, but we have been adding more and more people over the last few years. Most of our players are from Key Biscayne but we have a good amount who come from the mainland. We range in age from 16 to 60 (average is late 20's), mostly male. We are pretty liberal with the rules (ie. No hold/stall count or bricks) but most violations are penalized one way or another. 

     Any newcomers, from any skill range, are always welcome. If you are extremely serious about ultimate this is *NOT* for you. We believe in the spirit of the game and having a positive experience, no BS. 

     Feel free to text the phone number listed, or email me, if you want anymore information. 

***Lately, due to limited fields, we've been playing on the beach.

name: Frisbeeish Casual Pickup
description:
One of the friendliest and most family-friendly games in Austin, the Lake Creek pickup game is co-ed, every Sunday with decent weather, and runs about 10 to 12:15p. 

Please remember that this is a goofball game. Please dish the disc to the newbies when possible and be nice if they drop it. Parents, there are a lot of friendly kids whose parents play and who run around in a gaggle during the game. The field has swings, playsets, a portapotty, and a shaded blacktop.

Location: Lucy Read Pre-Kindergarten, near Northcross Mall. Parking: the school lots near 7510 Silvercrest. PLEASE DON'T PARK ON PINELEAF. But if you’re a parent with a lot of gear, it’s legit to park on the *west* side of Pineleaf. Any lightly-burdened player doing this will get to bring sliced watermelon to a summer game. Yum.

We also usually run a carpool from central Austin. Contact us if you'd like to get in on that.

name: Lincoln Park Ultimate Frisbee
description:
*Dress warm, in layers....we promise you'll find comfort in the chilly weather! Ah, the joys of a good winter sweat! *


To Bring:
-Cleats! If you got
em, most of us play with them.
-Water, snacks (stay hydrated yo!) *We do have occasional BBQ's
-Dark and White shirts for both sides (gray shirts make it tough..)

How we play:
-7 on 7 usually
-'Spirit of the Game' is very much a part of our game
-We try and AVOID 'last back' rule. Play 2-3 points, and play'em hard, then get off the field. Rotating is key.

-Players resolve their own calls
-We are a happy, boisterous bunch of goofs that work hard on the field and have a good laugh too. If this sound like you, c'mon out!

Thanks!

-'Spirit of the Game' is very much a part of our game
-We try and AVOID 'last back' rule. Play 2-3 points, and play'em hard, then get off the field. Rotating is key.

-Players resolve their own calls
-We are a happy, boisterous bunch of goofs that work hard on the field and have a good laugh too. If this sound like you, c'mon out!

Thanks!

name: Riverside in Austin, TX
description:
Starts at 12 p.m. "Frisbee time." Games often continue as late as 1:45 pm in decent weather. We never officially cancel. Expect a smaller crowd if the weather is really nasty (e.g., horizontal hail).
All ages, sexes and skill levels welcome. Novices, seasoned club players, old folks, etc. A friendly game but solid competition if you want to match up with those players. Bring a light and dark shirt. 
Likely spots are:
The most likely spot: Zilker Park fields north of Barton Springs Rd.
The 2nd most likely spot: Zilker Park fields on Robert E. Lee Rd.
Maybe: The Zilker Park field nearest the playground on the south side of Barton Springs Rd. It's the "rugby field" directly across from the most likely spot.
Unlikely: the Zilker Park fields on the south side of Barton Springs Rd., across the street from the botanical garden.
Don't despair. All these spots are within a few blocks of each other.

name: MSI Lunch-Time Ultimate
description:
We've been playing pickup ultimate during lunches for over 20 years on the Motorola Schaumburg campus. We're mostly comprised of MSI and former Motorola employees, but anyone with a positive attitude is welcome to join us for recess.

The address is 1301 E Algonquin Rd, Schaumburg, IL. Drive into the middle of campus until you see the big grass area and softball backstops. We show up just after noon and start about 12:15, ending at 1. 

Please bring a white and a dark (remember: grey is not a color). If you want water, you'll need to bring it--there are no facilities available. Some folks wear cleats, but a number go barefoot in the summer.

If you're interested in joining us, send us a message (ultdisc0003@gmail.com) and we'll add you to the poll for the next game. We play year-round if we have at least 8 (and sometimes 6 during winter).

description:

Fun-loving and enthusiastic pick-up on the modified soccer field at the Cooperstown Central School.  All ages and skill levels are welcome. name: Slacker Wednesday
description: Looking for a little mid-day, mid-week ultimate in the Los Angeles area? Come out to Oak Grove Park (AKA Hahamongna Watershed Park) in beautiful and scenic Pasadena, California, and join an LA tradition since 2002. The field is plush, parking is plentiful and close, and the game is dog- and beer-friendly. Lost a job? Can't find a job? Wouldn't want a job? Then join us every Wednesday, year 'round, for some slack disc in the sunshine. And remember our motto: "Slacker Wednesday -- it works because you don't." -jv

name: Oakland Pickup
description:
A friendly, regular rules game welcoming all skill levels. This game has a long (like 20 years) history, and often has new players as well as strong college and club players. Usually have both genders. Official start time for Sundays is currently 4:00pm - game starts  after that. Be patient.

Wed. Game currently, ON 5:30 official start - game shortly after typically.  Good turnout on Wed. often a second 5 on 5 field.

Games typically get going within ultimate-time half-hour, sometimes longer for Sunday. If gates are closed there is entry under the fence at Racine and in the middle of the park.

description:

This game is definitely on ultimate time - in the summer it may not get started until around 4.  All levels welcome.

For public transportation, go to www.mta.net and use the trip planner.  LA bus 333 goes down Venice Blvd. and drops you off two blocks from where we play.

Game is suspended during beach league - generally mid-October to early December

Come play with us. We welcome new recruits year round. Plus we are an awesome team with our main focus on having fun and achieving glory, rather than playing to win at all costs.

We train from 11am every Saturday year round right outside Clapham South.
And during summer we play pickup every Monday from 6.30pm until dark / beer.

All training & pickup sessions are free. The beer, unfortunately, is not.

We play in all the London Leagues - Winter, Summer and Indoors. And we also play in some fun tournaments every year. 

We have a yahoo group mailing list that you might want to sign up to.

Come play with us. We welcome new recruits year round. Plus we are an awesome team with our main focus on having fun and achieving glory, rather than playing to win at all costs.

We train from 11am every Saturday year round right outside Clapham South.

We have a yahoo group mailing list that you might want to sign up to.

pyramus-and-frisbee-subscribe@yahoogroups.com

Cheers and see you on the Common,
Nick

name: Outermost Ultimate & Cape Outermost Disc
description:
Outermost Ultimate is a loose band of core players who, with a constantly changing stream of summer visitors and summer folk, gather 1 evening a week in the summer for a game of pickup.  Skill level is anywhere from beginner to experienced, young & old, cleats or barefoot, official rules and, when necessary, summer rules.  

We play at Nauset High School (100 Cable Road, Eastham).  Park at the tennis courts and walk back the dirt path to the track.  Watch the Facebook posting for details about weather.

Bring plenty of water, a clearly dark/colored shirt, a clearly WHITE shirt, cleats if you've got them, and maybe bug dope because sometimes the bugs are just bad!

name: Toro Park Ultimate
description:
Weekly games almost every Saturday at Toro Park, just off of Highway 68.  We play on the first field (Badger Flats) you see just as you enter the park.  Free parking is available if you park outside of the park and walk in, otherwise there is an $8 per vehicle entrance fee.  Water and bathrooms available.

Easy going, yet competitive game.  We  welcome all skill levels.  

Usually we start around 10:30am and play until noon, not keeping score.  After noon, we play first to 5 and then go to lunch!

There is also a gmail group which we use to see if we have enough people to play a game on the upcoming Saturday.  If you have any questions, send me an email.

smiles,
Kenji

Bring a white shirt, a dark shirt (no grey!), water, and cleats.

description:

Monday & Thursday starting at 6 PM (March - October)
Saturday mornings at 11 AM (Year-round)

1) Shoes: soccer cleats aren't allowed, but turf cleats are.

Bring your best game, bring your best attitude, bring your friends (human or animal)!!!

name: Coalition Frisbee Workers
description:
Join us this Sunday for the friendliest game in town!

** 6/8/16 update: Great numbers lately (multiple subs)!  Meet @ 3pm, games typically starting 3:20 or so, usually playing until 5ish. Field conditions are hard and dusty, but play is friendly and spirited. **

Bring a light & a dark shirt (please skip grey & yellow!) - be flexible & ready to make matched teams for good, fun play.

This game plays every week unless canceled on the Facebook page.

This is a no-stress, friendly pick-up game that welcomes players of ALL experience levels, abilities, ages, and sexes.  We come to have fun and play hard – aggressive attitudes stay home, please.  New players always welcome!

We meet at the tree near Barrett & Jacksol - come introduce yourself!  There is a bathroom and water fountain at the park.

We play by current UPA rules, but defense marks up for a dropped pull (no turnover) and we generally go with "cool catch trumps close call."

name: Monday Lunch Goaltimate
description:
Goaltimate is a modified ultimate game that is played on a half field. Goals are scored when the disc is advanced through a large pvc arch. Originally considered a substitute for ultimate and used when attendance was low (can play with 6-10), goaltimate has now become its own sport with a loyal following of players across the nation including pickup, leagues, and tournaments. 

Welcome to San Luis Obispo Goaltimate! This game was established 07/2015. Currently the game is being played on French Park. (Directions to French Park: take Tank Farm off Broad heading towards Orcutt Rd, then take a right on Poinsettia, park will be on the left). We usually play by the baseball diamond.

Now that we are consistently playing at French-- the game is almost never cancelled due to weather!

This game is moderately competitive, but newcomers are welcome. Bring a light and a dark.

Sunday games: Little warmup and then games games games.

Who: 
Everybody who likes to play Ultimate. Beginners and internationals welcome!

Where: 
Gleisdreieckpark (East), next to the abandoned freight railway tracks. See google maps: https://www.google.de/maps/place/Park+am+Gleisdreieck
Subway station: Möckernbrücke (U1+U7). Walk south on Möckernstr. and you'll find the park on you right, climbing up some stairs. When you see old railway tracks, our field is to your left.

name: Blueberry Hill Park
description:
Check our page on Meetup.com to see our playing schedule in 2012; search for "Blueberry Hill Ultimate".

How we play:
*If you don't know how to play, we'll teach you the basics....all are welcome!

* We don't use force defenses, cup defenses, stacks, etc. We play a family-friendly game.

* We aim for easy going gameplay so you won't be given commands on how to run or where to play. Nobody wants to be told what to do.

* We don't keep stall counts as most of us throw in the first few seconds anyway.

* We welcome players of all abilities who make it a point to get everyone involved in the game. Don't make us have to remind you to throw it to your other, open teammates, even if they're not superstar players because, really, none of us are.

* Remember that ultimate frisbee is a non-contact sport. Rough play 
is not cool here.  Overly aggressive play will earn you a timeout.

* We usually have 7v7, sometimes a little more, sometimes a little less.

Sunday afternoon pickup ultimate on the sand at the north end of Coogee Beach. That's between the volleyball nets and the line of boats. Look for flying discs and bear with us if it takes a little while for everyone to turn up and for us to find a big enough spot for a real game.

Players at all levels are welcome to join us for a game, and Coogee is a lovely place on a sunny Sunday afternoon.

We move the start time to give us 2 hours before sunset, which is also when the beach starts to empty out. That moves between 2:30 in winter to 5:30 in summer with the daylight saving adjustment. 

To check we're playing and what time, check what we're saying by looking at the facebook page ( https://www.facebook.com/groups/coogeedisc/ - you can view this even if you don't use facebook ) or joining the email list ( https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/coogeedisc - make sure you configure it to send you email ).

description:

name: Ashland pickup
description:
Updated August 9, 2016:

We plan pickup Ultimate on Wednesday evenings at Ashland Middle School (corner of Walker and E. Main). Arrive 6 pm, pull 6:30. Game usually lasts until 8:30. Grass field.

We'll move back to N Mountain Park (also in Ashland, also pulling 6:30 pm) on September 7 for the Fall. Lights + amazing field.

Please signal your interest by joining us on Slack for free:
http://soupa.org/slack/ , to know if there is a game on any particular Wednesday.

Players range from 16 to 50+ and include both men and women; solid skills are represented but there's also an openness to new players.

Bring a light and a dark shirt.  Most players wear cleats, but this is not mandatory.

Some parents bring their children to hang out on the sidelines while they play.

We also often play on Sundays at 3 pm in Medford at Fichtner-Mainwaring Park. We also have seasonal leagues and hold a tournament in May.

more information:  http://www.soupa.org/

name: Ultimate Frisbee of Osaka
description:
If you're interested in playing with us in our pick-up games or playing with us in a tournament, drop me a line, or just show up in Umeda and wave your hands up and down and scream "Ultimate!" real loud and someone will call the police to take you away. 
UFO practices take place every Sunday afternoon, amidst the greenery of Yodogawa and its parklands. We meet on the southern side of the river at 2:00pm, which is an easy walk from Hankyu's Nakatsu Station (that's one local after Osaka). From the station, walk up some stairs and then walk straight (west) to the river and you should see some baseball fields next to the bridge on the left. We are past those baseball fields. It's only about a 500m walk. You will find us by noticing a lot of plastic flying in the air...
html_description:
Ultimate Frisbee of Osaka

Email: neubig@gmail.com
Website: http://www.dannygomes.com/ufo.html

name: Marble Hill Discers
description:
We are a mixed group of players who have been playing together for 6 years.  We try to play to the rules but have some of our own - and love it when more experienced players can come down and show us a trick or two!  We also warmly welcome beginners - young, old, male or female.  Everyone is welcome.  A drink after at the local is always encouraged!  Hopefully we work well for travelers who are just passing/working in London for a short time, and can't handle missing their weekly fix...

We play on the rugby pitches closest to Orleans road. Good for parking if you drive. 

PLEASE NOTE In the winter we play on a flood lit pitch around 15 minutes drive from our summer location. We play at The Heathland School in Hounslow (beware there is another heathland school!).

name: 52 Pick-Up
sunday_time: 2 p.m. in winter, 3 p.m. in summer
description:
52 Pick-Up is a year-round outdoor ultimate pick-up game in Damariscotta, Maine. We play on Sundays at 2 p.m. in winter, 3 p.m. in summer. Contact us before showing up in spring or fall to figure out which schedule we're on. Everyone, regardless of experience, is welcome. It's a great bunch of people who play year-round, even in deep snow, and we love when visitors show up during the summer tourist season.

To find us, go to the Great Salt Bay elementary school in Damariscotta and drive around to the back parking lot. We'll usually be on the field beyond the parking lot. If you have kids, there's a great playground for them, or they can play frisbee with us. If you show up on time and don't see anyone, wait a while. We're not very punctual...

name: Ultimate - Olmos Basin
description:
We have a casual game and have had it running for around eight years. Good mix of all skill levels. Good place for new people to get started playing. We tend to run with a few more than regulation rather than having people substitute to keep everyone playing the whole time. We usually run two games due to the number of people and occasionally 3 games at once. Usually were anywhere between 28-38 people on a given Sunday and a smaller game on Fridays. We play almost every holiday. Best way to get updates is our facebook group: 

https://www.facebook.com/groups/137436576315988/

We currently play from 5:30 Pm to 8:00 Pm on Sundays and currently on Fridays from 5:30 Pm to 8:00 Pm also. Fridays turnout is usually a little smaller and one game instead of two. 

Sometimes Olmos Basin Sports Complex (Soccer Fields) are flooded in which case we play on our backup fields at McCullough and Basse next to the baseball fields.

Come play some ultimate with us on a Sunday in the near future!

description:

We play on The Village fields, located at 8303 Southwestern Blvd, Dallas, 75206.

Sign up for the Dallas Ultimate yahoo group ((http://sports.groups.yahoo.com/group/dallasultimate) for updates, rain out info. etc.

All skill levels are welcome. We run 2 fields, the 2nd field generally is more competitive but anyone is welcome on either field. Bring a white and a dark shirt, gray is neither white nor dark.

In an effort to get everyone involved and keep the level of play high, you are requested to sub out if you're on the winning team for 3 points in a row (or 2 ridiculously long points). Nobody waiting? then keep playing. Losers, as always, run for the line.

name: Phnom Penh Sunday Pickup
fields: Grass!  Outdoor with trees nearby, a nice escape from the city.
cost: First time is free, ~$3 per play thereafter, or $40 for 3 month membership
description:
Come play pickup with us on Sundays at Northbridge International School Cambodia in Phnom Penh.

Sometimes we have league or drills before pickup, so check the mailing list for weekly announcements.

After pickup we usually hang out for a drink or two at the cafe next to the fields ($1 drafts, good fruit smoothies too).

We also hold the Big Phat Phnom Penh Hat Tournament every year around March 8 (International Women's Day).  The first hat was held in 2009.  We've held one every year since then with a rocking Saturday night party, slip n slide layout contest, and more.

This is a nice sized tournament where you will get to know everyone and you will find the Phnom Penh expats and Khmer people are out-of-their-way friendly.  We will likely give you sightseeing suggestions or maybe even show you around town if you are here for longer than the weekend.

Come for the tournament, visit Angkor Wat, then spend some time relaxing at a beach near Sihanoukville or one of the nearby islands!­

name: Anaheim Ultimate
fields: Modjeska Park, lit by street light and cone lights
description:
Co-ed Pick-Up Ultimate for ALL skill levels AND ages!

We are a group who welcome any and all skill levels. If you have never thrown a disc before, come join us! If you have played for a long time already, come join us! We play hard and enjoy competitiveness, but our main goal is FUN!

From 5 to 6, we sometimes play a non-Ultimate disc sport like Double Disc Court, MTA, TRC, Discathon, Disc Golf, Accuracy, or Distance. If we aren't doing one of the above, we're warming up and teaching throws.

The field does not have stadium lighting, so after dark we continue playing with light-up discs and lit cones until around 8:30 - 9.

We always meet at the same time and place, rain or shine. Please bring a black shirt and a white shirt, and cleats are recommended but not required. The only thing required is a good attitude!

description:

description:
Unlike many pick-up groups, this group plays year round.  During the summer, we play at Lost Creek Elementary school.  During the late fall and winter we get in some good light-up ultimate with LED wristbands and discs on the intramural fields at Rose-Hulman.

All games are organized via the Facebook group in the form of a role-call.  If enough people are able to play (usually at least 8 for 4v4 play) participants will meet at the specified place and time.  Occasionally times or locations may change so pay close attention to the Facebook group for the latest updates!

Location:  Lost Creek Elementary School -or- Rose Hulman Institute of Technology
Time of Play: 5:30-8:00 PM (M,W,F)
Facebook Group: http://www.facebook.com/groups/322709711158357/
E-mail Contact:  THUltimate@outlook.com
Level of Play:  Beginner-Intermediate (Newcomers and veterens welcome!)
Field Type:  Grass (Cleats recommended!)
Field Size:  Regulation (Playing field proper: 40x70 yards; 25 yard end zones)

name: Valley Ultimate
description:
Come on out and play some casual Ultimate Frisbee in the valley! We're a laid back, friendly group that is perfect for beginners and experienced players alike. All skill levels are encouraged to come out and join us.  We can teach you the game if you haven't played before.

• We play multiple short games. Each games typically last 30 minutes, for around 2 hours total. Feel free to come at any time.

• We typically go out for a small lunch after the game.
RSVP on meetup.com to get up to date event info. You're going to make some new friends and get some great exercise!  See you there!

~

We always have clean red and blue jerseys for teams, but you can bring one red and one blue shirt if you prefer.

description:
See our website.  Game start times varies, so join our email or cell TXT distro list(s) to be in the know!

On Weekends/Holidays & sometimes on rare Mondays, we play off-base in either Lusby OR at (rarely) John G. Lancaster park in Lexington Park, MD.

On THURSDAYS, we play after work on PAX base at the soccer field by the base Movie Theater. (You need a CAC card to get on base, but if you don't have access to base, send us an email with your cell phone#. We may be able to get someone meet you to carpool.)

"Game ON!" Email/TXT msg is sent out only if 8 or more people reply to our headcount Email/TXT saying they are coming.  So if you don't get a "Game ON!" email/TXT, it means we didn't get 8 people and game is cancelled. (If you change your mind about coming, be sure to send an email saying you are not coming ASAP.)

The pitches are getting busy and often booked by Tag Rugby, so just keep wandering until you find us.

Signup at the Yahoo Groups link for more info.
--

This incarnation of Ultimately Fabulous Frisbee has been going on the same spot since 1999.

Played every Monday night through the summer, check the email list in case it rains.

We do *not* take it seriously, the emphasis is on fun. Guys and girls come along, and newbies are encouraged to come along and bring their friends. We're very friendly. Don't worry if you can't throw a frisbee. Neither could I when I started, or most of the others.

name: Desert Ultimate
description:
In the Spring, we play at Hovley Soccer Field, with reserved lights and field.  On Mondays we are on field one and on Fridays, field 5 (the far south field).  In the Fall and Winter we are at Freedom Park in Palm Desert both nights.  From Memorial day until Labor day we play Mondays and Thursday evenings at the Civic Center park in Palm Desert. Saturdays starting 5:00 pm at the Civics Center park.  The exact dates for switching from one venue to another is imprecise.  The best way to tell is by finding Desert Ultimate on Facebook.

We play recreational Ultimate, meaning that there is a priority of getting everyone, including beginners, involved in handling to disc.

Sometimes, during the hot month, we play Sunday night in the dark with lighted arm bands and lighted discs.

name: Family Friendly Ultimate
saturday_time: 4:30 pm, 3:45 pm Nov - March, weather permitting
description:
This is a family friendly game with adults and kids. The game started a couple of years ago from local synagogue members and their families and has since grown into a nice group of regulars. We play with adults and children, max 4 kids and 4 adults per team, but usually less, especially when it is cooler.
The game is surprisingly competitive, but still lots of fun. All levels welcome for both adults and kids. For the little kids, we try to include them with some easy short passes (team keeps possession even if dropped), but for older kids and teens, it is the usual rules. Many of them have become better than the adults.

We play every Saturday in Ralph Field in White Plains at 4:30 pm, changing to 3:30 pm when we turn the clocks in winter.

name: HP Roseville Site Games
description:
We welcome beginners to very experienced players who want to have some fun while addressing the primary goal of non-contact exercise.   Our ages range from recent college grads to 55yrs+ with young teens joining the game when school is out (family style).  That being said our experience level is all over the map, but our play style is a balance of short to medium range throws with some hucks.  We attempt to balance skills to keep it fun and challenging for all.  

The game is on the Hewlett Packard Campus and open to all...dogs are no allowed unless service dogs.

Facilities include, locker rooms, showers, toilets and drinking fountains...also picnic benches and an area for the family to hang out.

Bring a dark and white tee shirt, cleats and don't be shy.  We play all year round so check the webpage for sign ups.  Occassionally we'll play 'box' if only 3 on 3.

name: Ultimate Frisbee Saudi Arabia
description: Hello everyone in KSA! In late spring of 2010, a small group of expats living in Khobar, Saudi Arabia, decided to take their love of Ultimate and start spreading the news and developing a league and interest in Saudi Arabia for this sport. The first games were played in the Arabian villlage and were 3 on 3. Over the year since, we have developed quite a following and play weekly pick-up games at Aramco Softball Hills Field#2 in Dhahran on the Aramco main camp. Currently they are Tuesday nights from 7:30-9pm. We are open to anyone interested in playing, whether it's your first time and you don't know what a frisbee is, or if you've been playing since you could walk.

name: VA Highlands Pickup
description:
This is a roving pickup game in the Arlington, VA area - field space can be hard to secure without a permit so we play on the best fields that are available, making an effort to keep it as metro-accessible as possible.

All skill levels welcome. Numbers are usually pretty good. Please check the Facebook group for details regarding location, potential cancellations, etc.; it is updated on a daily basis. Be sure to bring water, cleats, and a light and dark shirt.

Fields vary depending on availability and time of year, but the following are a few of the fields we use:
- VA Highlands Park
- Eads Park
- Long Bridge Park
- George Washington Middle School (Alexandria, VA)
- Carver Community Center

name: Lexmark
description:
Shadybrook Ultimate is still going, every Monday night (even through the winter!)

Big wide open fields. Cleats are definitely a good idea.  There are lights so we can always play until 8-8:30-ish year round, if we have numbers.

Game time is 6 but we will always start early if we have people there ready to go. Come join us!

All skill levels welcomed. This is a co-ed, friendly, but competitive game. Hope to see you out there.

This game is played on the property of Lexmark so the roads within "Shadybrook Park" aren't easily defined... but the game is in the far back  NW corner. If you know the area just keep driving back towards the softball fields until you see someone throwing a disc! If you are unfamiliar, contact me for detailed maps.

- stu

name: Spearfish pickup
description:
Description: A co-ed ultimate Frisbee pickup game in the Spearfish, SD area. All are welcome, beginners and professionals alike. This is a great group to get involved with if you want to exercise with fun people! Don't know how to throw a frisbee, or what ultimate frisbee is? Don't worry, we will be happy to show you. Just come by a little early while some of us warm up and we can show you the basics of the game, as well as a few tips on throwing a frisbee. Keep checking in here for updates on where and when we will be playing! 

In the spring/summer/fall we play at Spearfish High School on Sundays, Tuesdays, & Thursdays at 6pm. Thanks!

During the winter we play indoors at Black Hills State University
(fieldhouse). Wednesday & Fridays at 7:45pm-9pm.

name: SLO Tuesday Night Ultimate
description:
The best pickup in SLO County!

All skill levels welcome, games are high intensity but friendly with usually several club (or ex-club) players. There are usually plenty of subs and we typically play for 2 1/2 hours ish. Most people show up around 6pm to warm up, play starts promptly at 6:30pm. We play under lights most of the year.

Registration and a $10 per season payment is required and can be done online.  Players can register at any time during the season.  

Our pickup seasons run for 12-14 weeks Fall, Summer, and Winter with league play from mid June through the end of August. If you are interested in league play, contact pismobeachvet@gmail.com.  

If there is rain, look for an email or on Facebook with alternate field location - most likely Laguna Middle School. The rain hotline is 781-7301.

Bring a dark and a white shirt and water.

To register, go to http://slocity.org/parksandrecreation/

name: Keywees Ultimate
description:
Interested in playing Ultimate Frisbee!? 

We’ve organized a weekly game of Ultimate Frisbee right after work on the green field at Harmans Park (7605 Ridge Chapel Road, Hanover, MD 21076) on Wednesdays @ 5:15pm that is perfect for this sort of thing. Our season normally runs from April through October.

We're looking for more interest so we can split into set teams and organize a bracketed tournament! To start though, we’d like to see who’s interested in playing and how many of you there are. If you have questions e-mail Dalton Mackie at keywees.ultimate@gmail.com or just show up ready to play. We have a few discs and cones already on hand so just remember to bring a dark and light colored shirt.

Feel free to invite others and beginners are welcome!

name: Air Force Academy Pickup
description:
There are pickup games at the Air Force Academy on Tuesday and Thursday at noon. Games usually last until 1:30. The academy is open to the public, just have your driver's license to get through the gate. Games are on the cadet soccer fields. Take North Gate Blvd. Take left on Parade loop and a right onto Field house Drive. You can park in front of the Field House and walk down to the athletic fields. When the weather is bad, we play in the fieldhouse or the Holaday Center. To play you must be sponsored by a member of the DoD or employee of USAFA. To arrange a sponsorship contact Bob Sullivan.

Please e-mail Jimmy or Nathan from CSUN and they can get you in contact with Bob, if you have any questions.

name: 0° - Zero Degrees Ultimate
friday_time: 20:00 - 22:00 (At Avery Hill, NOT Royal Greenwich park. Call/email for information)
description:
We are a very friendly group of mostly pretty new players, guaranteed not to intimidate even the greenest of recruits!

In season, we play every Wednesday evening after work, from 18:15 until dark. Check out Facebook group for details, and come on over! Although it's midweek, we try to hit a pub afterwards too.


"0° 00' 00" - The First Frisbee Team in the World!"

Once there was an Ultimate Frisbee Team in Greenwich, South East London... by the light of the moon and under the watchful gaze of the Prime Meridian they would play and play... Then the group vanished without a trace.

Years later, a time came when other frisbee players happened upon that sacred ground, between the Stars and the Queens, and the gentle sound of an Ultrastar-175 gracefully spinning through the air was heard again amongst the rustling grass.

That time is now. 

That group is us. 

Join us.

name: Palo Alto Weekday Morning
description:
We're just a group that enjoys playing friendly, casual pickup games. We very open to beginners and have a range of abilities and ages. Some people play hard, but no one is very concerned about winning, etc., and it's fine if you're a beginner and drop the disc. Everyone plays even it means that one team might have one more person than the other. 

There is a second field available another game, if there are too many people for one game. 

We start warming up at 6:45AM and start playing at 7AM. Game ends at 8AM so people can leave for work. We play year-round.

We are in the middle of changing fields, but it looks like people prefer the Stanford IM fields. Contact me to get on the email list to make sure.

name: Boulder Lunchtime Ultimate
description:

We have great pickup at lunch (noon) Tuesday & Thursdays at Valmont City Park (intersection of Valmont and Airport Road). Often 2 fields and we play ~1.25 hours. Bring water, cleats, as well as white and dark shirts.

name: Thursday Lunchtime Goaltimate
description:
Goaltimate is a modified ultimate game that is played on a half field.  Goals are scored when the disc is advanced through a large pvc arch.  Originally considered a substitute for ultimate and used when attendance was low (can play with 6-10), goaltimate has now become its own sport with a loyal following of players across the nation including pickup, leagues, and tournaments. 

Welcome to San Luis Obispo Goaltimate!  This game was established 10/18/2012.  Currently the game is being played on French Park b/c we like the added element that a slight hill brings to the game.  (Directions to French Park: take Tank Farm off Broad heading towards Orcutt Rd, then take a right on Poinsettia, park will be on the left).  

Now that we are consistently playing at French-- the game is almost never cancelled due to weather!

This game is moderately competitive, but newcomers are welcome.  Bring a light and a dark.

name: Ultimate - Medford
description:
Updated August 9, 2016:

We play pickup Ultimate frisbee at 3 pm on Sundays in Medford at Fichtner-Manwaring Park (nice grass fields).

We also play pickup Ultimate at 6 pm on Wednesday evenings in Ashland at Ashland Middle School (summer) and North Mountain Park (starting Sep 7) , have seasonal leagues, and hold a tournament in May.

We're looking for more players to join our community.

Please signal your interest in joining us on Slack for free:
http://soupa.org/slack/ . This is how you will know if there is a game on any particular Sunday or Wednesday.

Players range from 16 to 50+ and include both men and women; solid skills are represented but there's also an openness to new players.

Some parents bring their children to hang out on the sidelines.

Bring a light and a dark shirt.  Most players wear cleats, but this is not mandatory.

Visit http://www.soupa.org/ for more information on all of the above.

name: Boston Frisbee
description:
Yes, we run three games a week.

Boston Frisbee is a fun, safe, all inclusive outlet for ultimate play.  We are beginner-oriented.

We don't keep score, we don't use stall counts, and we make up ridiculous rules all the time.

Please bring water, a WHITE and DARK shirt, and dress for the weather.

Typical locations are Russell Field in Cambridge, Cassidy Playground in Chestnut Hill, and Joe Moakley Park in Boston.  All the information is on our meetup site: http://www.meetup.com/bostonfrisbee/

name: Champ de Mars
description:
Ultimate Frisbee at Champ de Mars, in full view of tour Eiffel!

Where: 48.854070, 2.302525
Field: Dirt

We generally play Tuesday and Friday (more likely Friday) from 12:30 (12:40) - 1:25 at Champ de Mars.

This has been a regular lunchtime game for coworkers for the past 4/5 years, but it's always great to get new players! 

If you want to play, the only rule is to sign up on doodle. If there are 6 or more players by 12:00, game on! Yes, we will play even if there are 3x3. Be there!

If you sign in and can't play, please sign out before 12:00 so we know if there is a valid game or not. Bad spirit juju if you don't!

We usually get to the field around 12:30/12:40 at the latest, and play until 13:23 when we call 2 points before having to go back to work :.(

It's a pretty loose game, played on the dirt field next to the park. Safe as long as you don't lay out! The only strategy we play is play hard and have fun!

If you are local and want to be on the mailing list, send me an email.

name: CA Ultimate Frisbee
description:
Join us EVERY SUNDAY where we regularly meet at Brookside Park south of the Rose Bowl from 11am - 2pm. We represent all skill levels of play, and especially welcome new comers. Kickoff is at 11:30. We invite you to show up by 11 if you want to practice throws and technique. Our main goal is to have fun!

First time for Ultimate? Bring a pair of cleats or running shoes, sunscreen and a bottle of water. Also, bring a White, Dark, & Red T-Shirt (our idea of jerseys.) Next, just show up, we'll teach you the rules and show you how to play the game, it's easy and fun!

2nd Sunday of the month we meet at La Canada High School due to the Rose Bowl flea market. For update information check our Facebook page: https://www.facebook.com/groups/58686012761/

name: Ultimate at Antelope
description: Almost every Saturday afternoon for over 10 years running, ultimate has persisted in the greens at Antelope Park, Lincoln NE. It has a rich tradition in providing athletes with a unique canvas to play. Any person of any skill level is encouraged to participate. Congregate around the drinking fountains between the recreational center and the band shell at 2pm. Fountains only function in the Summer, so bring water accordingly. The occasional wedding or community event may force us to relocate to the adjacent field just southwest of the Naval memorial statue. Whether you've heard word or not, assume that it happens every week, rain or shine. Bring friends.

name: Cleveland West Side Pickup
description:
Join us every Tuesday at 5:30 for THE pickup game on the West Side of Cleveland.  We also play on Saturday mornings at 10:30.  It's highly advised to get on our email list to be kept alert of any cancellations/changes to games.  7000 Paula Drive, Middleburg Heights 44130 - Middleburg Hts Jr High (formerly Midpark HS).

Games are competitively casual (yeah, think about that one!) and all talent levels are welcome.  Be sure to bring water.  

While these games are fun and casual, a group of the attendees form Mojo Disc Squad, a rag tag bunch of 'gym rat' ultimate players who will travel to frisbee tournaments throughout the year.  If you're interested in competitive play, but don't have the time commitment/skill level to join Smoke Stack (CLE's club team), you may find Mojo a good option.  Just come out to a game and meet us!

name: Clearwater Beach Ultimate
description:
PLEASE CALL OR TEXT FIRST!!!  Lately we haven't always had numbers, and when we don't we call the game off and nobody is out there.

---

We play every Saturday afternoon until the sun sets over the water.

Meanwhile, we get serenaded by live music from the Palm Pavilion, and entertain the patrons eating on the deck. Afterward, join us for drinks and grub at the Palm!

We play by Wildwood rules, which means:

* 4 on 4
* The pull must land upside-down
* Stall count is to 6
* A foot touching the boundary line is in bounds (goal line is still not in)
* A throw from end zone to end zone is worth 2 points

We set up more than one field if there's good turnout.

name: Ultimate Cardio
description:
Ultimate Cardio is a fun new fitness class based on the dynamic sport of Ultimate Frisbee. It's a great way to get fit the fun way and make new friends. The 1 hour sessions combine fun games with dynamic exercises to make getting fit fun! The games and exercises are suitable for players of all abilities from complete beginners to experienced veterans. Everyone goes at their own pace so you don't need to be a super-athlete, you can just find a level that suits you. 
After the session we play Pick Up until it gets dark!
Contact Ian if you've got any questions or want more information.

name: Redlands Ultimate
description:
We encourage a fun, supportive atmosphere where everyone of all skill levels is welcome.  Our players range from beginner to experienced.  If you have never played ultimate before, we're a good group to get you started.  All you need is a bottle of water.  We usually start to gather around 5:30pm on Fridays and 10:30am on Sundays.  During the winter months when it gets dark early, our Friday games are glow-in-the-dark: we wear glow necklaces and play with a light-up disc.  

We play at Moore Middle School in Redlands, at the intersection of S Dearborn St and 5th Ave.  We typically play inside the running track, but if there are other people using that space, we'll probably be shifted off to the side a bit, but we'll be in that general area.

Feel free to join the Facebook group for updates or if you have any questions.  Hope to see you out there!

name: Long Beach Ultimate
description:
We are a beginner-friendly, laid-back, fun group of people who love ultimate!  We have been playing every weekend at or near Cal State Long Beach for the past 7 years or so, and have decided it would be nice to have some new faces show up.  We welcome men and women of any skill level!

Lately, we've been meeting at Hill Middle School, which is right around the corner from Cal State Long Beach.  The game is at 4:30pm on SUNDAYS.

Join our facebook group for another way to stay updated, and email me if you want to get on our mailing list.  Email me if you want to check if the game is still on, as we sometimes cancel if numbers are low.  Hope to see you out on the field!

description: Were just a group of people trying to have a good time! You should know we do play ultimate but its a very relaxed setting. For example, we dont have a stall, and boundaries are more like guidelines. We are a Co-ed group with mixed levels of experience ranging from club and college level players to people who have never played! Depending on the season, the range of people go from 10 to even 30 people. We enjoy meeting new people and welcome anyone who wants to play! name: Balboa Park (Sundays @ 10:30) with SD Frisbee Crew
fields: Grass but there are patches of dirt as well.  Cleats prohibited.
description:
We play every Sunday 10:30 & Thurs 5:00 (during daylight savings time) at 6th & Maple in Balboa Park. If our group were rated on a arbitrary scale of 1-10 (1 being beginner, 5 intermediate, 10 Pros) we would be a 4. We're mostly 20-30 young professionals. We're skilled enough to catch, throw, and run routes yet laid back/respectful towards each other to not yell/be aggressive to your fellow players.

We play 6vs6 due to field size. Stall count is 7. Don't really force too often. We tend to grind/swing plays and work on short game rather than hucking/throwing amubulance passes (though those happen too).

If you've played intramurals, college, or on a league, we're still fun to practice your throws with. Or if you just wanna check it out, feel free to watch.

Please bring a dark & white shirt (NO GRAYS) to even teams.

name: Rose Bowl Pickup
description:
Hi all,  Game usually starts around 2:30.  Currently one of the highest level pickup games in LA, but that depends on who shows up.  New players are welcome; but people will ask you to force, stack, and stuff like that.  

Bring a watermelon next time you come if you are the last person to arrive (or you just feel like it).  Or beer.  Beer is always good.  

Usually there's a short disc golf game before pickup.  Something to do as people show up.  Feel free to join, we use regular ultimate discs.

And finally, if the field is unavailable, the backup is La Canada HS.  If that's not available, it's across the street from the High school at hahamunga park.

Thanks,
Seth

name: Ultimate Maneuvers (Lexington Tuesday Ultimate)
description:
Hi everyone! We play casual pickup frisbee during the summer months (May to August). We play on the LHS football fields. 

We play pretty loose rules: loose-ish boundaries unless it's an end zone play. Don't keep score. Otherwise, it's normal rules (although we shy away from contact). It's mid to low level, although we have people who play BUDA/high school ultimate every time.

If you want to play, please request to join the group and one of the admins will approve it so you can participate in the polls. During summer months, we get about 12-18 people per game on regular weather days.

Ultimate Maneuvers (Lexington Tuesday Ultimate)

name: Fairbanks Ultimate Association
fields: grass in summer/indoor court in winter
cost: Pick up is free/ League play is $35 per season
description:
Winter indoor pick up is under way at the Student rec Center on the UAF campus-each Friday night. for more info-search Fairbanks Ultimate on Facebook.

FUA has pick up Ultimate starting in May and running through September before winter moves us indoors-Summer league kicks off in June with a hat tournament (the Sombrero Tournament) first week of June. Any interested players are welcome-just bring cleats, water and both a white and a dark T. 

Ultimate is played on the Rec fields on the campus of UAF in Fairbanks. But Thursday night league is played at the South Davis softball complex

Pick up (and league/tourneys) are played co-ed. Winter play is held Friday nights indoors at the student rec center on the UAF campus.

You wont find a better group of players to hang with anywhere. Fairbanks Ultimate is notorious for its hard play, its spirit and its friendly, yet competitive atmosphere. PLEASE LOOK US UP ON FACEBOOK;Search-Fairbanks Ultimate.

name: International DiscFits of Alameda
description:
Beginner-friendly co-ed pick-up game that has been going on since many years; age range is from teenagers to folks in their 50s.

We're all about having fun and exercise. We don't keep track of any score. If you can do a basic frisbee throw, you're good to go - we'll teach you everything else. Just come by and approach anyone, we will include you and match you with someone at your level/speed/age.

We have a few more serious players, too, and mostly do 1-on-1 defense so you usually will be matched with someone your own ability and speed.

Sundays are usually more busy, sometimes with kids included. Friday games are sometimes cancelled due to lack of players - ask to be put on our Teamsnap list to get notices about cancellations and field changes.

If no one's there at the start time, please wait 15 minutes - most folks are not on time.

If weekday games are on a public holiday, start time is 10am.

name: Dave and Greta's Minneapolis Sunday Pickup Ultimate
description:
This is a low-key game for people of all ability levels with a lot of beginners. No stall count. We encourage newcomers and experienced players alike to come join us. We are always looking for people to come check us out. Even if you're just passing through, come on by and waste a couple of hours with us! Kids and pets welcome. We play Sunday afternoons all year long, rain or shine. 3-5pm CST wintertime and 4-6pm CST summertime. Our field is the grass pitch located long Minnehaha Creek, on the east side of 34th Avenue South, just a block north of Minnehaha Parkway in South Minneapolis. It's a short 3 block walk west of the 46th Street Light Rail Station.

We also play Wednesdays at 6pm-dark, until as late in the year as we can!

name: Saturdays 11:00 Standley Rec Center
description:
We play pick-up ultimate on Saturdays at Standley Recreation Center, from 12:30 until everyone's gassed. 

All levels are welcome. We're all looking to improve, so as long as you don't suck on purpose and you don't pick on people less skilled than yourself, we'll be good to go. We like to have fun and friendships are formed.

Basic info: 
-We appreciate punctuality, but won't shoo you away if you are late.
-Dropped pulls are not a turnover
-Any other questions? Ask and we'll let you know.

name: Linköping Ultimate
description:
We usually have a great mix of ages, all levels of players and both genders. Most players are students at the Linköping University but we also have local veterans, national team players, exchange students and youth players. We are always happy to have new players and we make sure everyone get to know the basics and get involved in the game. We usually start with some throwing and drills and then play a game.

From late April until the beginning of October we play outdoors, default is the grassfield in the middle of "Rydsskogen" at "Motionscentrum" Sunday 17.00-19.00 and Tuesday 18.00-20.00.

Indoor Nov-April:
- Wednesday (probably at "Kungsbergshallen") 21:30-23.00.
- Sunday at "Rydsskolans sporthall" (address Björnkärrsgatan 15 D) 19.00-21.00.

Please visit our facebook group for the latest updates!

name: Tuesday Night Ultimate
description:
We play casual games every Tuesday evening, and can be found near the central rocks (either just north of them, or up the hill on the West side) on the large field at Zilker Park.

All ages and skill levels welcome. Our games tend to be on the less competitive end of the spectrum, but we still get plenty of running and good times in. We do our best to help out newer players, so don't be afraid to show up even if you have never played before!

When people stay late enough, we will break out glow sticks and an LED frisbee and play after dark.

Nobel Athletic Area
7299 Shoreline Dr
San Diego, CA  92122
United States

tuesday_time: 18.45 - till dark or we get tired
description:
Clapham Frisbee runs a social game Tuesday evenings from 18.45 in Summer.  We will be near the cricket pitches between Cedar's Road and the Kiosk on Clapham Common. (We tend to move around a little bit depending on where the footballers and Ozzie rules folk are.)

We play every Tuesday as long as there is enough daylight (April to Sept). In winter we play on Sundays if we can get the numbers. 

All abilities are welcome - from experienced to beginners! Bring friends, family and flatmates along!

Discs are provided just bring water and appropriate footwear. Games are FREE and followed by Kiosk or Pub visit.

During Winter we play on Sunday's at 13.00-15.00.

name: Columbus Inidiana Ultimate
description:
2016.05.11 Update: Thursday Games are active if and when weather permits (It has been a very wet spring so far). Please ping the email address if you would like to be added to the mailing list.

We play very good spirited pick-up. We have some experienced players and some good athletes, but cater to ALL age, gender, skill and fitness levels... we play w/o keeping score until we get tired, then call a game to 5 or 7, then play one more competitive point "for ALL the Marbles"! We try to keep the web site updated, currently we play at Mill Race Park in downtown Columbus. 

Our season ends when DST ends.

We request all players bring both a white shirt, a dark shirt (please avoid grey) and water. Turf cleats advisable.

name: Hudson Pickup Ultimate
description:
This is a co-ed, social, recreational pickup game attended by players from all over Metrowest.  We play on an awesome well-groomed full-size soccer field just west of I-495 in Marlborough (adjacent to Hudson, near I-495/I-290 interchange).  Afterwards we go to a nearby restaurant for dinner & beer.  Our typical skill level is a little below what most leagues would accept, and player age ranges from early 40s to early 60s.  We have a number of women players and more are welcome.  We're just out for a good time (no scoring, plays, or stacks). Some weeks we have two adjacent games.  A few of us bring our kids. The teenagers play, the younger ones watch.  

Details and signup are on the website http://www.hudsonultimate.org/

name: Frisbot 3000
description:
Frisbot is a very friendly game, generally played Saturday mornings on the north side of Chicago. All skill levels are welcome, and we have players ranging from absolute beginners to league veterans. We're currently playing at River Park (Foster between California and Kedzie).

If you want to play, go sign up for our polling system at frisbot.com. You'll get an email notice with links to RSVP for the game. name: Carmel Valley
description:
This is a very active game, so you do not need to email to ask if we are still playing.  There isn't an address for the park, just put "Carmel Grove Park" into your navigation.  

If you get there and the fields are closed, we have two backup fields.  During the summer, we use Carmel Del Mar Park, which you can see in the map above.  If school is in session, or that park is closed, we go to Carmel Creek Neighborhood Park, please note that the public part we play at is off Carmel Center Drive, not Carmel Creek Rd.

Please bring a dark and a white shirt so that we can try to make the teams even.

We usually play 3-4 games during our lunch time.  All games are to 5 points.  We play standard USA Ultimate rules, with the exception of a 7 stall count instead of 10.

We play on grass fields.  You are encouraged to wear cleats, however, they are not required.

description: We play a LAID-BACK Ultimate Frisbee game on Tuesday nights @8:00 p.m-(Frisbee time).  Stall counts 10.  We play 4 on 4, to 8 on 8 (: No SUBS! (if there are more than 8 on 8, we'll play 2 games maybe lol)  We play at the UA mall on University just east of Cherry (we play West of Cherry in front of the student union when a basketball game is going on).  If you see a glow in the dark disc then you found us!  No need for dark/white t-shirts just bring water (cleats not necessary).  We use different colored glow sticks to differentiate between the teams.  We call blatant travels (if you're new and pick up your pivot foot, no one is going to call travel).  UA winter/summer break = low numbers! Free parking in the open lot just south of the field located between Cherry and 4th St (its North of 4th street)

cost: Donations to pay field fee but absolutely not required.
description:
All levels, fun pickup.  Contact strongly discouraged.

Season starts 3/15, weather and field conditions permitting.

Runs from DST start in March to DST end in Oct/Nov.  Game always on unless weather or field problem.  Time is earlier in spring and fall due to earlier sunset. name: High COuntry Ultimate
description: We are a group of mountain folk who like to throw plastic. You down? Come join! Bring your friends. We have people of all skill levels; no experience, lots of experience, doesn't matter. Age; preferably high school age and older, but we are willing to incorporate kiddo's at some point in the night. If you are planning on coming a dozen times or more, please bring $100 to solidify your spot. If you are just dropping in for one night please bring  $10 if you can. If not, no worries, but this is a non-profit organization so any little bit helps! Other than that, all you need is cleats, lite and dark shirt, water, and tons of high-5's. So come check out what we mountain folk are all about and we'll see you at the bottom!

name: North County Ultimate - Harbor Beach
contact_name: Aaron W., Dave W., Mat H.
description:
Beach game on the sand of beautiful Harbor Beach in Oceanside, California!  Games are a mix of skill levels, ages and male/female.

The game is held at Lifeguard Tower #14.  Park in the free all-day parking lot on the east side of the train tracks, in one of the free 2-hour spots on the west side of the tracks, or pay $8 or so to park in one of the closer spots to the beach.  Walk west past the shops and restaurants until you get to the beach then walk north about the length of 2 football fields to the game site.  We'll be just north of the jet ski / boat washdown area and adjacent to the restroom facilities.

Bring a light and dark shirt, some water, and a towel if you care to take a dip in the Pacific Ocean after the game.

PS:  In Sept. 2015 we changed play to Saturdays to accommodate the new Sunday game at Encinitas Community Park at 9am.

Thanks!

saturday_time: 3:00pm or 4:00pm, depending on daylight savings time
description:
Great game on Saturdays at the Stanford Oval!

Friendly and newcomers are very welcome. It's competitive in the sense that we often run hard and play with a stack, but we want everyone to have fun and aren't so worried about who wins etc.

Email rshane@gmail.com to join the mailing list, because games don't always happen, but they usually do.

There can sometimes be a few ultimate games on the Oval. We play between the sidewalks, and on the end of the Oval farthest from the quad and Memorial Church.

Come join us! Apologies if I don't get back to you right away, but I will get back to you! Also, the game starts at 3pm when daylight savings time is off and 4pm when daylight savings time is on.

name: Legends Sports Complex
description:
Very rules-relaxed pickup games on Monday nights.

We try to split up teams to make them as even as possible.  If we have more than 15, we split to three or more teams and play "Cutthroat" where if your team gets scored on, the next team comes on.  Keep track of your points and we play to 10.

A lot of players are newbs with less than 2 years experience, so rules are on the relaxed side, but anyone can call any foul and it's respected (as long as you're respectful when calling it).

Fun group, welcoming to strangers and new players wanting to learn.

Bring your own water, water fountains are on the other side of the gym, slows the game down when people are out for water.
